Now, to translate this into code, we shall embark on a journey through the land of Java, where the syntax is our guide and logic our compass. Here is a snippet that finds valid parentheses and counts them:

```java
import java.util.Stack;

public class ParenthesesCounter {
    public static int countValidParentheses(String s) {
        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();
        int validCount = 0;

        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') {
                stack.push(c);
            } else if (c == ')') {
                if (!stack.isEmpty()) {
                    stack.pop();
                    validCount++;
                }
            }
        }

        return validCount;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "((()))()";
        System.out.println("Number of valid parentheses: " + countValidParentheses(input));
    }
}
```

